}}'''''Thunderchopper''''' is a 1986 video game published by Actionsoft. The DOS version was by [[Sublogic]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Thunderchopper |journal=The Games Machine |date=February 1990 |issue=27 |pages=53 |url=https://archive.org/stream/the-games-machine-27/TheGamesMachine27#page/n52/mode/1up}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Thunderchopper'' is a game in which the player pilots a Hughes 530 MG Defender.<ref name="CGW44"/>

==Reception==
M. Evan Brooks reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Thunderchopper'' lacks the elan and panache that one would have expected."<ref name="CGW44">{{cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |title=Choppers!: Evan's Fighting Gunships |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=February 1988 |volume=1 |issue=44 |pages=15}}</ref> [[Zzap!64]] gave a positive review, giving an overall rating of 83% and calling it "A polished, technically impressive flight simulator."<ref name="Zzap!64">{{cite magazine |last= |first= |title=Thunderchopper |magazine=Zzap!64 |date=January 1988 |volume=1 |issue=33 |pages=21}}</ref>

